# Localization Rules

## No hardcoded user-facing text

Flutter and Unity user-facing strings must use localization keys.

**Exceptions:** debug-only developer output, technical identifiers, approved brand names, data from backend localization fields.

## Language architecture

Version 1 must support architecture for English and scheduled Indian languages per product rules. Individual language completion may be staged; do not assume English-only layouts.

## Requirements

- Stable localization keys
- Preserve placeholders in translations
- Support text expansion; avoid fixed-width buttons for translated text
- Support Unicode correctly
- Plan for RTL where applicable
- Validate missing keys
- Align Flutter and Unity terminology using `docs/product/revo_olympics_terminology_glossary.md`

## Prohibited

- Building sentences through concatenated translated fragments
- Using English text as the localization key
- Embedding user-facing text in images where avoidable
- Assuming all names use Latin characters
- Truncating text without accessible alternatives

## Review checklist

- [ ] User-facing strings use keys
- [ ] Placeholders preserved
- [ ] Glossary terminology consistent
